@page "/blog"

<PageTitle>About Me</PageTitle>

<div class="blog-container">
    <article class="blog-post">
        <header class="blog-header">
            <h1>Meet Me!</h1>
        </header>

        <div class="blog-content">
            <div class="intro-section">
                <img src="/pictures/me.jpeg" alt="Photo of Marcus" class="profile-photo" />

                <div class="intro-text">
                    <p class="lead">
                        Hi! My name is Marcus, I’m 25 years old, and I live in Odense. I’m the type of person who feels
                        most at home when I’m either writing code, being active, or doing something outdoors (especially
                        if it involves ducks).
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <section class="content-section">
                <h2>Who am I?</h2>
                <p>
                    I'm Marcus. A student born with a curiosity for how things work and a pretty competitive mindset (mostly with myself).
                    I come from a family with five siblings in total, so you could say I learned early on how to cooperate,
                    speak up, and not give up when things get a little chaotic.
                </p>
                <p>
                    I’m also a huge fan of chihuahuas. They have way more personality than their size suggests, and honestly,
                    I love that.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="content-section">
                <h2>What do I do?</h2>
                <p>
                    Most of my time is split between studying and improving as a developer. I love programming because it’s a mix of
                    creativity and logic. One moment you’re designing an idea, and the next you’re hunting down a bug that was caused
                    by a missing character.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Outside of school I’m very active. I enjoy working out in general, and I’m proud to say I’ve benched over 110 kg ;)
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="content-section">
                <h2>Why am I here?</h2>
                <p>
                    I’m here because I want to build real things that people can use and because I enjoy the constant learning that comes
                    with tech. My goal is to keep getting better at software development, strengthen my professional skills, and be the kind
                    of teammate people can rely on.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="content-section">
                <h2>Let’s connect!</h2>
                <p>
                    If you see me around (online or in real life), feel free to say hi. I’m always up for talking about chihuahuas,
                    training, or sharing the best spots in Odense to go feed ducks :)
                </p>
            </section>
        </div>
    </article>
</div>

<style>
